    <!-- PROTEIN SOURCES DEEP DIVE -->
    <div class="ing-box">
      <h4>Protein Sources Compared: Which Type Is Best for Your Goals?</h4>
      <p>The source of protein in your gummy determines its amino acid profile, absorption speed, and effectiveness for your specific goals — whether that is muscle building, joint health, weight management, or skin improvement.</p>

      <div class="vs-strip">
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Whey Protein Isolate</strong>
          <p>90%+ protein by weight. Complete amino acid profile with 2.7g leucine per 20g serving. Fast absorption (30-60 min). Best for muscle building and post-workout recovery. Minimal lactose. The top choice for athletic performance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Whey Protein Concentrate</strong>
          <p>70-80% protein by weight. Complete amino acid profile. Slightly slower absorption than isolate. Contains more lactose and fat. More affordable. Equally effective for muscle building when total daily intake is matched.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Hydrolyzed Collagen</strong>
          <p>Incomplete protein (missing tryptophan). Rich in glycine, proline, and hydroxyproline — the building blocks of skin, cartilage, and tendons. Not effective for muscle protein synthesis due to low leucine. Best for skin, joint, and gut health.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Plant-Based Blends</strong>
          <p>Pea + rice blends provide a complete amino acid profile. Lower leucine per gram requires 25-30g doses for equivalent MPS stimulation. Suitable for vegan athletes. Growing formulation quality is closing the gap with whey.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

