    <div class="tested-box">
      <h3>How We Tested These Protein Gummies</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Purchased independently.</strong> All 19 products were purchased at full retail price. No product was provided by any brand, and no manufacturer was informed of this evaluation.</li>
        <li><strong>Verified protein content.</strong> We cross-referenced supplement facts panels and requested certificates of analysis to confirm actual protein content per serving against label claims. Products with third-party verification scored higher.</li>
        <li><strong>Evaluated protein source quality.</strong> We assessed each product's protein source for amino acid completeness, leucine content, and absorption characteristics based on published literature on whey, collagen, and plant proteins.</li>
        <li><strong>Conducted taste and texture testing.</strong> Five testers evaluated each product blind for flavor, sweetness balance, gummy texture, and aftertaste. Scores were averaged to minimize individual bias.</li>
        <li><strong>Calculated macro efficiency.</strong> We computed protein per calorie, protein per gram of sugar, and cost per gram of protein to identify products that deliver the most protein with the least nutritional trade-offs.</li>
        <li><strong>Assessed real-world convenience.</strong> Portability, packaging resealability, shelf stability, and serving size practicality were evaluated for gym bags, office desks, and travel scenarios.</li>
